<dl id="n25104b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n25" href="#n25104b">N25 (VI.B.15)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n25all.htm#n25104b"> 104(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> called for his good hat</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Then the duke <mark>called for his good horse</mark>&mdash;a better could not be found. It had been sent him by a king of Spain, out of very great friendship. Neither arms nor the press of fighting men did it fear, if its lord spurred it on. Walter Giffard brought it. The Duke stretched out his hand, took the reins, put foot in stirrup, and mounted; and the good horse pawed, pranced, reared himself up, and curvetted. <small> Edward Creasy, <a name="ECFD" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#ECFD"><cite title="source">The Fifteen Decisive Battles of the World</cite></a> (1915) 210</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c14063k" href="c14all.htm#c14063k">VI.C.14:063(k)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
